CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, September 1, 1962 reads: "PIONEER'S FAMILY - Mal R. Goode, one of Pittsburgh's most prominent pioneers now is joining the ABC news department as a staff member.  Here he's shown with his lovely family.  Left to right, front row: Ronald, Mal, Mrs. Goode and Rosalia.  Standing: Roberta, Richard, Russell and Robert" (Daughter Roberta was inserted into published photo).
TitMainTitle: Group portrait of Goode family, including first row: son Ronald, Mal Goode, Mary Lavelle Goode, daughter Roberta; back row: sons Richard, Russell, and Robert, posed outdoors in front of their home in Belmar Gardens
